mainEntity.name: What laser parameters are optimal for Urethane Composites?

acceptedAnswer.text: For Urethane Composites, we recommend 1064nm wavelength at 100W power with controlled pulse duration for optimal cleaning without substrate damage.

mainEntity.name: Is laser cleaning safe for Urethane Composites?

acceptedAnswer.text: Yes, laser cleaning is a non-contact process that preserves the integrity of Urethane Composites substrates while effectively removing surface contaminants.

mainEntity.name: What applications benefit from Urethane Composites laser cleaning?

acceptedAnswer.text: Urethane Composites laser cleaning is ideal for Cleaning Of Urethane Composite Parts For Surface Preparation Before Painting, Removal Of Contaminants From Urethane Composite Aircraft Components, and other precision manufacturing applications requiring contamination-free surfaces.
